webpackJsonp([0xfbc0fee432df300],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/html-attributes-lang.json":function(a,n){a.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>Lang</h2>\n<p>In HTML, Lang tag is used to declare the language of the whole or a part of a web page.</p>\n<h3>Examples</h3>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-html"><code><span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>html</span> <span class="token attr-name">lang</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>en<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>html</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>The lang attribute can also be used to specify the language of a specific element:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-html"><code><span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class="token attr-name">lang</span><span class="token attr-value"><span class="token punctuation">=</span><span class="token punctuation">"</span>hi<span class="token punctuation">"</span></span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n  फ्री कोड कैंप\n<span class="token tag"><span class="token tag"><span class="token punctuation">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class="token punctuation">></span></span>\n</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>In the above example, “hi” denotes the Hindi language. Similarly, you can use “en” for English, “es” for Spanish, “fr” for French and so on.</p>\n<p>Refer to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes">ISO 639-1</a> for the appropriate two-digit Language code.</p>',fields:{slug:"/html/attributes/lang/"},frontmatter:{title:"Lang"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/html/attributes/lang/"}}}});
